profile:
I have been a Carpenter for the past 10yrs. I have never had any complaints' about my work. Prior to this I was Foreman for Building Homes right from bottom to top. There is nothing that I have not done in Carpentry. I have worked both inside and outside. I have laid hardwood floors (not the click-lock) walls, windows, cupboards, adding another room, stairs (both standard and serpentine) I build decks, sheds for outside, boat launches, boat house's, shingling. Have given estimates' and have been very close to what I had said, I am a pleasant and personable person.  I can do blue-prints as well if needed  . This is not to be rude, I just have to keep numbers' in my head. I work alone or if I feel I need an assistant I always have someone on stand-by. professional in mannerism, respectful, customer is always right, always on time. Should someone have an emergency I do not leave the job I am doing, I tell this person I can be there between 6:00 pm - 8:00 p.m.
I am efficient, personable, down to earth, I take pride in my work!
